# Keep the build context small and never ship host-built artifacts into an image.
# node_modules is the big one: its native binaries (better-sqlite3) are built for the host,
# and copying them over a fresh in-image install breaks the pnpm symlink tree.
**/node_modules
.git
.github
.phases

# Build outputs — rebuilt inside the image. Incremental build state (.tsbuildinfo) lives next to
# tsconfig, outside dist; shipping it makes `tsc -b` think referenced projects (contracts) are
# already built and skip emitting their dist, breaking the web build. Never ship it.
**/dist
**/build
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local state and secrets. .env is mounted at runtime (env_file), not baked in.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-*
*.log
